mentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1158.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Shardwurm Bile</span><hr size=1> I've been wandering around the shardwurm cave killing anything that moves for a couple of days now and have yet to get my first bile.  I was told that there is a way to tell which wurms have bile on them?  Can anyone tell me how, or if any of the types of wurm have a higher chance of dropping bile?  <br>
<br>
Thanks <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=shustric>shustric</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(1/30/03 6:07:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1158.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Shardwurm Bile</span><hr size=1> Hunt at night - the wurms with bile glow.  I would kill in the caves until night and then go outside.  Eventually I just killed everything I saw since they were probably on the same spawn table as the ones that had bile.<br>
<br>
I got a few biles in the caves, but more in the area south of the caves, and I think the weaker wurms (forget name, young shardwurm maybe?) dropped it more often, though i'm not sure about that.  GL!<br>
<br>
Shustric, 62 Mage of The Shadow Order, Lanys <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nucci01>Nucci 01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 108<br> <font color=#333333>(1/30/03 7:07:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1158.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Shardwurm Bile</span><hr size=1> Forget the caves, hunt only at night just South of the caves, they roam past there all the time. We got 3 in 30min for a shaman friend last night til it turned daylight, then got the other 2 the next in-game night. The biles are definitely the easy part of the 5th shawl too so be ready for some time in Velks. Good luck.<br>
<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=465781">Master Nucci</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xymryk>Xymryk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 228<br> <font color=#333333>(1/30/03 7:49:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1158.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Shardwurm Bile</span><hr size=1> Thanks, I actually got my tailoring up to 125, then I got my Threads from Velks, and saved the bile for last, hearing that it was the easy part.  But I had been getting discouraged after no drops.  <br>
<br>
Thanks for the help.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=feninie>Feninie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 114<br> <font color=#333333>(1/30/03 8:46:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1158.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Shardwurm Bile</span><hr size=1> a bit late, but hey.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.eqtraders.com/quests/fifth.htm">www.eqtraders.com/quests/fifth.htm</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
has a section on how to see if the shardwurms have the bile or not (they glow).  <br>
<br>
Personally, I couldn't be bothered with that.  As people have pointed out, hunt the section south of the caves.  I just went on a killing spree, took about 2 hours to get my five.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=skildpade>skildpade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 145<br> <font color=#333333>(1/31/03 11:04:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1158.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Shardwurm Bile</span><hr size=1> Getting the biles can be really annoying. I was lucky and got mine rather quickly, but while helping some friends it took forever.<br>
<br>
I would not go around looking for glowing wurms but rather bonk every one I see,, because 1) if there are none up, there will be none up and 2) while the drop isn't spectacular, they still drop pp, spells and other stuff to pay for your time. Just don't kill the brothmother and the named wurm.<br>
 <p>nmee - commander of mudhills<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=407265">nmee's magelo</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xalmat@themagicianstower>Xalmat</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 596<br> <font color=#333333>(1/31/03 3:32:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1158.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Shardwurm Bile</span><hr size=1> When going after my bile, i just did the entire cave in one big loop. Takes longer, but the cash you make will help fund the &quot;Gotta get my Tailoring up&quot; budget. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=abdielalazrad>Abdiel AlAzrad</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#333333>(2/2/03 1:34:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1158.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~irasfel/_uimages/EVO3_26470.gif Height=151 Width=113></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Shardwurm Bile</span><hr size=1> It can really take a while.  To hell with day, night, or anything else heh.  Done it twice, best results were just going with the field in back of the shardwurm cave and massacring every shardwurm I could find.  Sometimes for quite a while they just don't spawn with the stuff, it can happen.  Just keep mashing every one of the big @#%$ you can find and don't fuss about glow/time/whatever.  Mind you if it DOES happen to be night and you do see one that's glowing wander by while you're on another one, disengage the pet and go get it, or just nuke it to death.  Otherwise just play shardwurm genocide, hand out white scale pants to low level casters, and yawn - could be a long haul.<br>
<br>
Hraefn Nevermore <p>&lt;BR&gt;<br>
